<br>
I am going to respond to this, as this is indeed a point of reason I said what I said. <br>
<br>
-----<br>
&quot;Mystus, if you had provided those same rods to, say, a wizard(and I'm not saying your should have, just if you had), they would done alot more nuking damage then you.&quot;<br>
-----<br>
<br>
What I did was by my using MY OWN skills and no one elses, I did more damage than anyone else USING MY OWN skill. Yes a wizard WITH mod rods might do more, but that wizard is not using HIS OWN skill, and that is offense that is LOST and not gained between BOTH the wizard and magician if that magician has to make rods for the wizard. In short, FAR more offense can be provided if the wizard nukes and uses his gather mana spell (or prehaps given a rod before the battle from a kindly mage) and the magician using his pet and nuking and then rodding self back up and then nuking some more than if only the wizard nuked and the magician just provided rods to that wizard. <br>
<br>
-----<br>
&quot;Its the rods, not the mage. Remember that. With T-Rods and healing support *ANY* class with a reasonable nuke can rack up insane DPS.&quot;<br>
-----<br>
<br>
I will have to disagree with you on this, providing healing classes with additional mana DOES NOT provide extra offense in DPS, but it does serve well in KEEPING ALIVE the people that are fighting in very long duration encounters. The point here is of any class using HIS OWN spells and skills, magicians can provide more offense than ANY class, I estimate that a magician EVEN WITHOUT the ancient nuke, focus items, external healing, or critical hits would SUSTAIN 116dps during a encounter, and even more during normal XP group situations, and THAT IS ALSO not including what the pet did. I would like to see another class do that. I can see magicians sustaining 200+dps between him/herself and the pet using focus items and criticals and using the correct tactics, and even more if a group shaman provided a occasional torpor or a cleric CE. Wizards are king of fast damage, there is no dispute over that, necros are king of mana effectiveness (also necros should NEVER die if they play them right), but magicians are the king of overall offense.<br>
<br>
Yes indeed, IT IS the magician that can make or break a battle. Indeed YES we can make use of THAT spell more than other classes can if you use them correctly. Rods are nice, but without the magician they are NOTHING. Belittling yourselves to say that rods is all a magician can do is shortsighted. Verant never designed this game to be ONLY winnable with mod rod2s, and always remember we are a class that can fill several roles, and there is more than one way to win a tough battle. Too many people are content in relying on OTHER people's tactics and not figure out a better way of doing a encounter and THIS is why we have such a preception problem nowadays.<br>
<br>
Anyway thats how it is...it is up to you on how you wish to play your class, just dont let ANYONE else tell you how to play your class. We have several roles we can fill, don't be content in just fullfilling only one of those roles.<br>
<br>
